                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="25769" author="luke" created="Tue, 28 Aug 2007 04:02:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This isn&apos;t really a bug, since the idea is that if you configure conversion of request URLs to lower-case prior to matching, then you should specify the match patterns in lower case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, I&apos;ve changed PathBasedFilterInvocationDefinitionMap to convert the secure URLs to lower case if convertUrlToLowercaseBeforeComparison is set to true. This will prevent any accidental use of upper-case letters in the configured secure URL from preventing a match. So&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CONVERT_URL_TO_LOWERCASE_BEFORE_COMPARISON&lt;br/&gt;
PATTERN_TYPE_APACHE_ANT&lt;br/&gt;
/secureURL.html=&amp;lt;some filter chain&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;will now match a request for &quot;/secureURL.html&quot;, even once it has been converted to &quot;/secureurl.html&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
